-- Ford and Mazda to start new Thai car plant
-- 
-- Tue Oct 9, 2007 5:15am EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2007/10/09/us-mazda-ford-factory-idUSTKV00291420071009

 

 TOKYO  (Reuters) - Ford Motor Co ( F.N ) and Mazda Motor Corp ( 7261.T ) will build a new car factory in Thailand with a capacity to build 100,000 cars a year, Mazda said on Tuesday. 

 The factory will begin operations in 2009, it said in a statement.